In the MATTER of H. L. J. OIL COMPANY, Bankrupt. Barbara E. STEWART et al., Appellants, v. E. A. LYNCH, Trustee, etc., Appellee. No. 6678. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 23, 1932. Frankley & Spray, L. W. Frankley, and Joseph A. Spray, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. Raphael Deehter and A. L. Wirin, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee. Hy Schwartz and Joseph J. Rifkind, both of Los Angeles, Cal., amicus curias.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, it is ordered the appeal herein be dismissed with prejudice and without costs; mandate forthwith.
